notesStmt.note: Shelomoh Kohen ben Yosef Kohen ben Mordekhai Kohen: inscribed, folio 1v.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: The Muḳadimat, or introductions (in Arabic and Hebrew), to the weekly parashiyot of the Pentateuch, by Shemu᾿el ha-Rofe al-Maghribi in three uniform volumes (volume 1).

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 17; written lines: 17; Uniform layout. Visible ruling with a mastara. Initial words of each section written in larger characters, preceded with a title page (see e.g. folio 224r, 240r, etc). Catchwords on every verso. The biblical verses are given with punctuation.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Square and semi-cursive Oriental script of the 17th century. Avraham ben Mordekhai ha-Kohen: inscribed, volume 2, folio 220v and volume 3, folio 126v. Avraham ha-Kohen wrote the present manuscript for his son, Yosef. The name of the latter is inscribed under the title of each Muḳadimah.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine title: 'Samuel ha-Rofe. Mukaddimat. Vol. I. Arabic & Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2482'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), a antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 08 July 1882: inscribed, folio [315v].
